{
  "stem": "1141.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Trucks-- certain places they had to stop, because the English were approaching from one side.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Americans were bombing, coming.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And the Russians were coming.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they were like taking people from one side to another so they can save themselves.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And some of the Gestapo, while we were on the way they were changing clothes into civilian clothes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's when we realized that there's something going on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's when we decided, perhaps, let's try to stay alive so the world would know what-- what happen.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And so we-- that's what we did.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I prepared myself emotionally, that if I am-- if I remain alive, I want to tell the world what a so-called-- in the 20th century-- such barbaric, inhuman, cruel people, doctors, can do to people.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So-- so we just decided.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But when my real breaking point was when I arrived to Bergen-Belsen, and I contracted typhoid.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I lost my hair.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I didn't-- there was at one point where we wanted to know-- I didn't remember anything-- where, who I really was.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because at the time, the temperature was-- must have been so high that my lips were just peeling.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The skin was coming off.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my-- the bruises from-- from the beating apparently, and the bottom of my feet were completely-- the skin was just coming off.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there were mountains and mountains of dead people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So everybody was walking around, or some of them were laying down.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you walked a few steps, and you laid down again.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
